</P>
<P>
	   The budget also proposes the biggest expansion in government health care
since the creation of Medicare by providing health insurance to at least 5
million of the 44 million Americans not now covered.
</P>
<P>
	   The president also wants to expand Medicare to help the elderly pay
prescription drug bills and allow persons 55 to 65 to buy into the program.
</P>
<P>
	   The Washington Post reported in Monday's editions that in addition to
proposing $160 billion over 10 years for general drug coverage for the needy
elderly, Clinton also will propose a $35 billion program to help those who need
to take particularly expensive kinds of medicine.
</P>
</TEXT>
