<HEADLINE> Lovett Performs at Benefit Concert  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    COLLEGE STATION, Texas (AP) -- Music stars Lyle Lovett and Robert Earl Keen
performed a benefit concert at Texas A&AMP;M University for the victims of last
year's bonfire accident and their families.
</P>
<P>
	   About 10,000 people attended Sunday's emotional concert, which began with a
display of news footage from the Nov. 18 accident that killed 12 people and
injured 27 others.
</P>
<P>
	   Organizers hoped to raise more than $100,000 for the Bonfire Relief Fund
established by The Association of Former Students to help offset medical and
other costs associated with the accident.
</P>
<P>
	   The concert at Reed Arena was sponsored by the association and Town Hall, a
student committee in A&AMP;M's Memorial Student Center. Lovett and Keen were
roommates while attending A&AMP;M in the late 1970s.
</P>
<P>
	   The reason behind the collapse of the 59-foot stack of bonfire logs remains
unknown.
</P>
</TEXT>
