	   Kennedy, 67, was admitted to Sibley Memorial Hospital on Sunday after
experiencing a fever and cough the previous evening, spokesman Will Keyser said.
</P>
<P>
	   ``He is in good spirits, he is resting comfortably and he felt good enough
to watch the America's Cup race last night,'' Keyser said Sunday.
</P>
<P>
	   The senator's son, Rep. Patrick Kennedy, D-R.I., was at a House Democratic
retreat in Hot Springs, Va., when he learned of the illness and flew back to
Washington, said his press secretary, Larry Berman.
</P>
