<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-07 13:03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading heavily
today on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock Market.
</P>
<P>
	   The defense contractor said it expects to post second-quarter earnings of 80
cents per share. Analysts had expected Litton to earn $1.05 a share. Litton
cited costs for two development programs in its advanced electronics segment.
</P>
<P>
	   Gold prices have surged in recent days after Placer Dome, one of the world's
leading gold producers, said it will stop selling borrowed gold as a hedge
against lower prices. Other gold producers are believed to be considering
similar strategies.
</P>
<P>
	   BB&AMP;T Corp. agreed to buy One Valley, the largest bank-holding company
headquartered in West Virginia, for $1.2 billion in stock. BB&AMP;T has been
expanding rapidly in the past decade, acquiring 40 banks and thrifts, 32
insurance agencies and 12 small finance companies.
</P>
<P>
	   The development bank plans to start offering stock trading on the Internet.
ICICI promotes the development of capital markets in India.
</P>
<P>
	   Morgan Stanley Dean Witter launched coverage of Ciena with an "outperform"
rating. Ciena designs equipment for fiber-optic networks.
</P>
<P>
	   The company, a provider of software products, announced a
multimillion-dollar contract with 3Com Corp. TCSI said 3Com will license its
Catalant network management framework and will use it as a core technology.
</P>
<P>
	   The company revised downward its previously reported financial results for
the second and third quarters of 1999. Sykes said the restatement was due to
delays in the recognition of revenue in connection with certain software and
service contracts.
</P>
<P>
	   The company has agreed to acquire Avesta Technologies Inc., a closely held
maker of software that helps companies manage electronic-commerce networks, for
about $343 million in stock. Visual Networks makes software for managing
Internet networks.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
