<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-07 13:23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S., N. Korea Consider New Talks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- With at least two remains of American soldiers newly
discovered in North Korea, officials from both countries indicated progress
towards talks on a joint recovery operation to find more Americans killed during
the Korean War.
</P>
<P>
	   North Korea, after initially reporting it had discovered the remains of 415
Americans, now says it has found only ``four or five.'' U.S. officials -- who
rejected the original report of hundreds of remains as untrue -- say they
believe North Korea has so far accounted for just two soldiers in the latest
discoveries during bulldozing operations at a reclamation project near Unsan.
</P>
<P>
	   A Pentagon statement Monday said U.S. officials are proposing a resumption
of talks with North Korea, which were cut off in December after North Korea
sought economic assistance in exchange for a joint recovery operation. The talks
had been held in Berlin.
</P>
<P>
	   Li Gun, a North Korean envoy at the United Nations, said Monday he could
make no announcement, but added that resumed talks are being discussed in North
Korea.
</P>
<P>
	   Li said there were some ``technical mistakes'' in the original report of 415
bodies, saying, ``We have four or five remains.''
</P>
<P>
	   Pentagon officials have said they hope to send a small team of forensics
experts from the Army's Central Identification Laboratory in Hawaii. Li has said
U.S. officials would be welcome in North Korea to review the new discoveries.
</P>
<P>
	   U.S. officials believe the earlier North Korean references to 415 remains
reflected a U.S. estimate of how many Americans were killed on the battlefields
near Unsan, 60 miles north of Pyongyang.
</P>
<P>
	   About 8,200 American servicemen are listed as missing from the 1950-53
Korean War. Over the past three years, joint recovery operations with North
Korea have unearthed 42 sets of remains.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-02-07-00 1323 </TRAILER>
