1997, an IMF official said today. The Thai economy is growing these
days, not faltering. Five percent growth is expected this year. The
repayment of the first $200 million will mark a symbolic end to the
regional recession, which struck Thailand first in July 1997 and
hit one country after another. By last year, world financial
authorities had declared the crisis largely over. The Bank of
Thailand will pay the installment in November,
</P>
