<HEADLINE> Sen. Kennedy To Remain Hospitalized  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Sen. Edward Kennedy, D-Mass., is suffering from a flu-like
illness and will remain hospitalized for the next several days, his spokesman
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
	   Kennedy, 67, was admitted to Sibley Memorial Hospital in Washington on
Sunday. He is being treated for a cough, muscle aches, chills and a fever,
spokesman Will Keyser said.
</P>
<P>
	   Victoria Kennedy issued a statement saying her husband is feeling better and
``itching to go home.
</P>
<P>
	   ``But he is still running a temperature, and his doctors and I have
convinced him that another few days of rest is the best treatment,'' she said.
</P>
</TEXT>
