<HEADLINE> Dow Ends Off 58.01; New Nasdaq High  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks diverged in familiar fashion today, with technology
shares leading the Nasdaq composite index higher for a sixth straight session
while blue-chip industrials slumped.
</P>
<P>
	   The Nasdaq rose 76.40 to 4,320.54, coasting past its previous record of
4,244.14, set Friday.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones industrial average fell 58.01 to 10,905.79. Broader stock
indicators were narrowly mixed.
</P>
<P>
	   The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 slipped 0.23 to 10,963.57.
</P>
<P>
	   Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 7-to-5 margin on the New York
Stock Exchange, with 1,775 down, 1,247 up and 496 unchanged.
</P>
<P>
	   NYSE volume totaled 915.13 million shares as of 4 p.m., vs. 1.03 billion in
the previous session.
</P>
<P>
	   The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies rose 6.87 to 532.39.
