<HEADLINE> Chicago Exchange Halts Trading  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    CHICAGO (AP) -- Trading was halted Monday on the Chicago Board Options
Exchange due to technical problems, officials said.
</P>
<P>
	   The stoppage lasted from just after 9 a.m. to about 11:30 a.m., said
spokesman Gary Compton. He said it resulted from computer software problems, but
did not elaborate.
</P>
<P>
	   The outage was unrelated to a water main break that caused some flooding in
downtown Chicago, Compton said.
</P>
<P>
	   Trading at the Chicago Board of Trade and the Chicago Mercantile Exchange
was unaffected.
</P>
<P>
	   The CBOE is the world's largest options exchange.
</P>
