<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   Monday, Feb. 7, 2000
</P>
<P>
	   Dow Ends Off 58.01; New Nasdaq High
</P>
<P>
	   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks diverged in familiar fashion today, with
technology shares leading the Nasdaq composite index higher for a
sixth straight session while blue-chip industrials slumped. The
Nasdaq rose 76.40 to 4,320.54, coasting past its previous record of
4,244.14, set Friday. The Dow Jones industrial average fell 58.01
to 10,905.79. Broader stock indicators were narrowly mixed. The
Nasdaq, dominated by technology stocks, has risen more than 5
percent so far this year, while the blue-chip Dow industrial
average has fallen more than 5 percent. Gary Campbell, chief
investment officer at The Commerce Funds in St. Louis, said fears
that interest rates will rise sharply this year are weighing
heavily on investors' minds, pressuring the vast majority of
stocks.
</P>
