service using the new format adopted by many Web site operators to
provide mobile phone users with access to the Internet. AOL said
today that the trial service will be offered free to AOL Europe's 4
million members by the end of February in partnership with mobile
telephone makers Nokia and Ericsson. AOL Europe is a joint venture
that's equally owned by America Online and the German media
conglomerate Bertelsmann.
</P>
<P>
