</P>
<P>
	   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Dedicated number crunchers can read the
federal budget online. President Clinton's $1.84 trillion proposed
budget for 2001 is available at www.gpo.gov/usbudget. The Internet
site includes several budget documents, among them the budget
itself, the Citizen's Guide to the Federal Budget and several
supporting documents. This is the sixth time the federal budget has
been made available via the Internet and officials say it is the
earliest it has been posted.
