<HEADLINE> Pitt Player Said Arrested For Drugs  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    PITTSBURGH (AP) -- University of Pittsburgh basketball player Isaac Hawkins
was arrested Monday on charges involving marijuana possession, according to
broadcast news reports.
</P>
<P>
	   Hawkins was arrested at his apartment after neighbors complained of a strong
odor of marijuana, KDKA-TV reported.
</P>
<P>
	   Police found marijuana in Hawkins' apartment, according to WPXI-TV. He lived
in the city's Oakland neighborhood, near the Pitt campus.
</P>
<P>
